ss=\"number\">9</p>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"digit\">\n		<p>#</p>\n		<p class=\"number\">0</p>\n		<p class=\"number\">1</p>\n		<p class=\"number\">2</p>\n		<p class=\"number\">3</p>\n		<p class=\"number\">4</p>\n		<p class=\"number\">5</p>\n		<p class=\"number\">6</p>\n		<p class=\"number\">7</p>\n		<p class=\"number\">8</p>\n		<p class=\"number\">9</p>\n	</div>\n</div>\n</center>\n<div id=\"question_code\" style=\"height: 295px;\">class BruteForce\n{\n	public static void main(String[] args)\n	{\n		int i=0;\n		/*\n			how to add 1 to i\n			i = i + 1;\n			i += 1;\n			i++;			\n		*/\n		// for( start ; range ; increment )\n		for(i=0 ; i&lt;100 ; i++)\n		{\n			//The value of \"i\" will be 0~99\n			//check the output \n			System.out.println(i);\n		}\n	}\n}\n</div>\n<p style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 18px\">\nTry all possible password and CRACK this lock!\n</p>',1,'BootCamp',5,'2013-02-21 18:16:34','2013-03-22 02:11:51','lib/Robots/BootCamp4.rb','2468'),(15,'no name',NULL,'<style>\np { text-align: left; padding-left: 10px; font-size: 15px; }\n#field tr,#field td{ width: 30px; height: 30px; text-align:center; font-weight: bold;\n</style>\n<h2 style=\"\">Minefield!</h2>\n<p>You need to make a software for a mine remover robot.<br>\nThe enemy soldier is a lazy man, so he placed mines in a pattern<br>Here is an example minefiled</p>\n<center>\n<table id=\"field\" border=\"1\">\n<tbody><tr><td></td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td>1</td></tr>\n<tr><td></td><td></td><td></td><td></td><td>1</td><td></td></tr>\n<tr><td></td><td></td><td></td><td>1</td><td></td><td>1</td></tr>\n<tr><td></td><td></td><td>1</td><td></td><td>1</td><td></td></tr>\n<tr><td></td><td>1</td><td></td><td>1</td><td></td><td>1</td></tr>\n<tr><td>1</td><td></td><td>1</td><td></td><td>1</td><td></td></tr>\n</tbody></table>\n</center>\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">\nIn order to remove mines, print x any y coordinate of the mine in this format: \"x:y\", \"6:1\"<br>\nThe top-left coordinate is (1,1)<br>\n<b>The dimension of the Minefield is 100 by 100. </b>Your robot only has enough power to remove the mines. <br>So.. You must only dig the places with a mine.</p>\n<p><b>ps.</b> make sure to read response inputs to avoid buffer overflow</p>',1,'Bank',2,'2013-03-10 05:39:55','2013-03-10 08:01:21','lib/Robots/Bank2.rb','BOMB bomb BOMB~\n');
